				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 25 Jun 2020 05:28:56 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>General note, I believe standard format for clinical documentation for numbers that don't have associated units is to write out numbers less than 10, and put digits for numbers 10 or greater. And always put numbers for stuff with units. So for example:</p> <ul> <li>Two apples</li> <li>16 wildberries</li> <li>Three sticks of goat butter</li> <li>7 ounces tabantha wheat</li> <li>10 cups cane sugar</li> <li>etc.</li> </ul> <p>ETA: for the sake of consistency, pretend those measurements above are in metric. d:</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
